
# Ring Topology

## Description
The ring topology connects each device to two other devices, forming a closed loop. Data travels in one direction (or both in dual-ring systems).

## Characteristics
- Data flows sequentially through each device.
- More reliable than bus topology, but a single device failure can disrupt the network.
- Suitable for small networks with simple requirements.

